Tribune Online  Vice-Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Kogi State, Kola Ojo, has died.Ojo, a legal practitioner, was said to be playing tennis at the Sports Centre, Ogudu GRA in Lagos when the incident occurred.A statement by the Publicity Secretary of PDP in Kogi, Mr Bode Ogunmola, said Ojo was immediately rushed to a hospital but was pronounced dead by doctors on duty, the News Agency of Nigeria reports.Ogunmola described Ojo as a “reliable pillar of the party.”